# =============================================================================
# APEX AI SPORTS PREDICTION ENGINE - COMPREHENSIVE API CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# This file contains ALL APIs used for 100% real data predictions
# See SETUP_GUIDES.md for detailed setup instructions for each API

# =============================================================================
# TIER 1: ESSENTIAL FREE APIs (Required for basic functionality)
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THE ODDS API - Betting Odds (FREE: 500 requests/month)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign up: https://the-odds-api.com/
# Free tier: 500 requests/month (no credit card)
# Coverage: 80+ sportsbooks, 30+ sports
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 4
ODDS_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API-FOOTBALL - Sports Data (FREE: 100 requests/day)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign up: https://dashboard.api-football.com
# Free tier: 100 requests/day (no credit card)
# Coverage: Football, Basketball, Hockey, Tennis + comprehensive stats
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 5
API_FOOTBALL_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENWEATHER API - Weather Data (FREE: 1,000 calls/day)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign up: https://openweathermap.org/api
# Free tier: 1,000 calls/day
# Used for: Environmental factor analysis
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 6
WEATHER_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# TIER 2: WEB SCRAPING APIs (For comprehensive intelligence gathering)
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE CUSTOM SEARCH API - Web Scraping (FREE: 100 searches/day)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign up: https://programmablesearchengine.google.com/
# Free tier: 100 searches/day
# Used for: Scraping news, stats, injuries, tactical analysis
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 1
# Note: This unlocks real web scraping from Google for all sports intelligence
GOOGLE_SEARCH_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_SEARCH_CX=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REDDIT API (PRAW) - Social Sentiment (FREE: 100 req/min)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sign up: https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
# Free tier: 100 requests/minute (completely free)
# Used for: Fan sentiment, community discussions
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 3
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=apex-sports-bot/1.0 by u/YourRedditUsername

# =============================================================================
# TIER 3: SOCIAL MEDIA APIs (Optional but recommended for sentiment analysis)
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TWITTER/X API v2 - Social Sentiment (PAID: $100/month for Basic tier)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ⚠️  NOTE: Twitter API is NO LONGER FREE for reading data
# Free tier: Write-only (1,500 tweets/month)
# Basic tier: $100/month (10,000 tweets/month read access)
# 
# Alternative FREE option: TwitterAPI.io ($0.15 per 1K tweets, pay-as-you-go)
# 
# Sign up: https://developer.twitter.com/
# Setup guide: See SETUP_GUIDES.md Section 2
# 
# ONLY add these if you subscribe to Basic tier ($100/month)
# Otherwise, leave blank and system will use Reddit + other sources for sentiment
TWITTER_API_KEY=
TWITTER_API_SECRET=
TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN=
TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN=
TWITTER_ACCESS_SECRET=

# =============================================================================
# APPLICATION CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000

# =============================================================================
# DATABASE (Optional - for production)
# =============================================================================
# Railway/Replit auto-provides this when you add PostgreSQL database
# Leave blank for development (uses in-memory storage)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:port/database

# =============================================================================
# SETUP PRIORITY
# =============================================================================
# For MAXIMUM functionality with $0 cost, set up in this order:
#
# 1. TIER 1 (Essential - All FREE):
#    ✅ The Odds API (500 req/month free)
#    ✅ API-Football (100 req/day free)
#    ✅ OpenWeather (1000 req/day free)
#
# 2. TIER 2 (Web Scraping - All FREE):
#    ✅ Google Custom Search (100 searches/day free) - HIGHLY RECOMMENDED
#    ✅ Reddit API (unlimited free) - HIGHLY RECOMMENDED
#
# 3. TIER 3 (Social - Optional):
#    ⚠️  Twitter API ($100/month) - Only if you need Twitter sentiment
#    ✅ Alternative: Use Reddit + Google News scraping (FREE)
#
# TOTAL COST FOR FULL FUNCTIONALITY: $0/month
# (Twitter is optional - Reddit + Google provide similar sentiment data)
#
# =============================================================================
# RATE LIMITS SUMMARY
# =============================================================================
# The Odds API:        500 requests/month  (~16/day)
# API-Football:        100 requests/day
# OpenWeather:         1,000 requests/day
# Google Search:       100 searches/day
# Reddit API:          100 requests/minute (6,000/hour)
# Twitter Basic:       10,000 tweets/month ($100/month)
#
# With these FREE tiers, you can generate:
# - ~16 predictions per day (limited by Odds API)
# - Comprehensive data gathering for each prediction
# - Full social sentiment analysis (via Reddit + Google)
# - 490+ advanced factor analysis
# - Zero cost
#
